GAUTENG cops are searching for suspects after four people were shot and injured in Eldorado Park on Wednesday, 8 June. According to Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo, at about 12pm, three suspects arrived in a silver-grey sedan and started shooting randomly next to a flat in the area. ALSO READ: ‘Printer kills a man’, company sued! “Four people were injured after sustaining gunshot wounds and three of them, including two pupils, were taken to a hospital. They are in a serious but stable condition,” Masondo said in a statement. He added that the fourth victim sustained minor injuries, and that the motive for the shooting could not yet be confirmed. He appealed to anyone with information to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111.